description: Returns a paginated list of objectives from the Amazon Web Services Control Catalog. You can apply an optional filter to see the objectives that belong to a specific domain. If you don't provide a filter, the operation returns all objectives.

parameters.name: ObjectiveFilter
parameters.description: An optional filter that narrows the results to a specific domain. This filter allows you to specify one domain ARN at a time. Passing multiple ARNs in the ObjectiveFilter isn't currently supported. Domains (list) --- The domain that's used as filter criteria. You can use this parameter to specify one domain ARN at a time. (dict) --- The domain resource that's being used as a filter. Arn (string) --- The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the domain.

nested_params.name: Domains
nested_params.description: The domain that's used as filter criteria. You can use this parameter to specify one domain ARN at a time. Passing multiple ARNs in the ObjectiveFilter isn't currently supported.

nested_params.name: Arn
nested_params.description: The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the domain.

nested_items.name: Objectives
nested_items.description: The list of objectives that the ListObjectives API returns.

nested_items.name: Arn
nested_items.description: The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) that identifies the objective.

nested_items.name: Arn
nested_items.description: The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the related domain.

nested_items.name: Name
nested_items.description: The name of the related domain.

nested_items.name: CreateTime
nested_items.description: The time when the objective was created.

nested_items.name: LastUpdateTime
nested_items.description: The time when the objective was most recently updated.

nested_items.name: NextToken
nested_items.description: The pagination token that's used to fetch the next set of results.
